<span class="header1">PUBLIC SERVICE</span>
<p>People who do well in this field are good leaders. They also want to provide some sort of service to the community.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">School Principal</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1387.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="School Principal" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A school principal is responsible for the day-to-day management of the school. As a principal, you would work very closely with teachers to make sure that students were being taught well. You would also work to keep students' parents and the members of the community satisfied.  The school board would hire the teachers and other employees, but you would interview them and make an assessment of them before they were hired.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most states require a principal to have at least a Master's Degree. Some prefer principals to have a Ph.D. and coursework in school administration. State teaching certificates are needed for any occupation in education. Principals and teachers are expected to be students themselves. They must take courses to improve their skills and knowledge.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A principal can make between $75,000 to $85,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Government Legislator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1403.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Government Legislator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A government legislator works with other elected officials to pass laws. The purpose of these laws is to make improvements or solve problems. It is possible to serve as a state or federal legislator.  In either case, those who lived in your community would vote you into office.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Legislators do not have to have a degree, but most people who are elected do have a degree. The most common degrees are law, public administration, and political science. In addition, people vote for candidates who have experience in planning. They also prefer legislators who can negotiate and motivate other people.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary can range from $20,000 to $71,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Police Detective</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a police detective, you would investigate crimes. You would try to find out what happened and who was involved. This is an exciting occupation. But it can be a dangerous job too.  To do this job well, you must be able to look at a crime scene and take in as much information as possible. You also must be a good listener so that you can take in information while a witness or suspect is talking.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Local police departments prefer to hire those with a Bachelor's Degree. To get a job with a state bureau of investigation or the FBI, you must have a degree. Detectives must pass a written exam.  They must also meet certain physical requirements.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $31,000 to $80,000.</blockquote>

