<span class="header1">MANAGEMENT</span>
<p>The occupations in this field are for people who like to oversee the work of others.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Hospital Administrator</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a hospital administrator, you would be responsible for the day-to-day running of a health care facility such as a hospital, clinic or hospice. You would be in charge of hiring employees and budgeting money. You might also help to raise money to keep the facility going. To do well in this job, you need business skills.  You also need leadership and people skills.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Master's Degree for this job. This degree might be in hospital or health administration. It might also be in public health.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $40,000 to $175,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Hotel Manager</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/43096.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Hotel Manager" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Hotels are an important part of the community. The person who runs a hotel is called a hotel manager. As a hotel manager, you would be responsible for making sure the guests are comfortable during their stay. One of the most important duties you would have is to make sure that the employees are doing their jobs properly.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in hotel and restaurant management for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $35,000 to $80,000+ a year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Assistant Restaurant Manager</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/43129.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Assistant Restaurant Manager" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Restaurants are very busy places. They have many different activities going on at the same time. The restaurant manager is responsible for making sure that the restaurant runs smoothly. But sometimes he/she needs an assistant to help. As an assistant manager, you might choose and price menu items and help in hiring the staff. You would do what the manager asked you to do. Many managers start as assistant managers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Employers look for those who work well with others and have experience in the restaurant business. A Bachelor's Degree is preferred, but is not required.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $30,000.</blockquote>

