<span class="header1">BUSINESS & INDUSTRY</span>
<p>If you like to be challenged mentally, you may want to consider this occupational field. The occupations in this field need people who are good at solving problems.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Corporate Lawyer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1366.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Corporate Lawyer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a corporate lawyer, you would work for a large company.  You would use your knowledge of the law to advise executives.  You would tell them how to best protect the company and stay within the laws that govern business.  You would also gather and communicate information to other legal professionals or clients.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To become a lawyer, you need a Bachelor's Degree plus three years of law school.  Lawyers must pass a written test known as the "bar exam" also.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $35,000 to $300,000+.  Salary depends on the size and wealth of the company.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Personnel Consultant</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1370.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Personnel Consultant" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy helping people in practical ways, you might become a personnel consultant. As a personnel consultant, you would find job opportunities in the community.  You would then find people within the community to fill these jobs. You would interview the person to be hired.  You might also test the person, using an instrument like the Interest Inventory that you took.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A personnel consultant can make as much as $80,000 a year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Retail Salesperson</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CG/1302.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Retail Salesperson" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When you go into a department store, you may have someone who comes to you and asks, "May I help you?"  This person is a retail salesperson. A retail salesperson answers questions that customers ask and helps the customer decide on what to buy. He/she also "rings up" the sale on a cash register or computer. Sometimes he/she is asked to restock shelves or racks.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Companies provide on-the-job training for this job. They may require special knowledge for people who want to work in technical sales positions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average salary may range from $16,000 to $36,000 per year.</blockquote>

